**Stop.** Do not take any action until you have read this entire file from top to bottom.

### Mandatory steps

- **Read the file from top to bottom**
- **Take no actions until the file is read**
- **Follow the instructions in the file**
- **Make decisions based on the information in the file**
- **Read and understand `<linked-tools-file>`** — mandatory in **`Workflow_ReadTools`**

### Scope (mandatory)

**All <domain> work must follow this workflow.** <Out-of-scope handoff rule.>

### Workflow layout (mandatory)

- **`Workflow_Start`** — first section (entry).
- **`Workflow_<RelatedName>`** — middle sections; execute top to bottom unless **`JMP → Workflow_<SectionName>`**.
- **`Workflow_End`** — last normal section.
- **`Workflow_Error`** — mandatory global error handler (immediately after `Workflow_End`).
- **`Workflow_<ErrorName>`** — optional specialized error sections (only after `Workflow_Error`).

### Primary workflow sequence

| Order | Section | Purpose |
|-------|---------|---------|
| 1 | **`Workflow_Start`** | Scope and entry |
| 2 | **`Workflow_ReadTools`** | Read tools index; decide which tools apply |
| 3 | **`Workflow_GatherUserErrorInfo`** | Intake context; prompt user until sufficient |
| 4 | **`Workflow_CollectLogs`** | Plan and run tool-based evidence collection |
| 5 | **`Workflow_Diagnose`** | Root-cause analysis; validate hypothesis |
| 6 | **`Workflow_Report`** | Traffic-light tables + user selection |
| 7 | **`Workflow_End`** | Completion criteria |

